    <div xml:id="PN327-intro">
      <p type="edition">tiṇaiyum tuṟaiyum avai
      </p>
      <p xml:lang="en" type="translation">  
      </p>
    </div>
    <div xml:id="PN327">
      <lg type="edition">
<l>erutukā luṟāa tiḷaiñar koṉṟa</l>
<l>cilviḷai varakiṉ pulleṉ kuppai</l>
<l>toṭutta kaṭavarkkuk koṭutta miccil</l>
<l>pacitta pāṇa ruṇṭukaṭai tappali</l>
<l>ṉokka loṟkañ coliyat taṉṉūrc</l>
<l>ciṟupul lāḷar mukattavai kūṟi</l>
<l>varakukaṭa ṉirakku neṭuntakai</l>
<l>yaracuvariṟ ṟāṅkum vallā ḷaṉṉē.</l>
</lg>
<lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
<l>Who, because the puny heap of a little ripe millet</l>
<l>that had been thrashed by the young men without undergoing the feet of the bull</l>
<l>failed at the point when the famished bard had eaten</l>
<l>the rest of what was given to those attached whose due it was,</l>
<l>in order to remove the destitution of [their] kinfolk in his village</l>
<l>talked in the assembly before little mean men</l>
<l>[and] begged for a loan of millet, the paragon</l>
<l>is a powerful man who holds out [even] when the king comes.   </l>
</lg>
    </div>
  </body>
